We then selected sources which had luminosities corresponding to $\geq1.0$~L$_{\rm H\alpha}^*$({\textit{z}}) and reaching up to $\sim 50$\,$L_{\rm H\alpha}^*$({\textit{z}}), with number densities in the range 10$^{-3.2}$\,Mpc$^{-3}$ to 10$^{-6}$\,Mpc$^{-3}$. Our luminosity limits roughly correspond to (observed) fluxes greater than $\sim3$, $\sim2$ and $\sim1.5\times10^{-16}$\,erg~s$^{-1}$~cm$^{-2}$ for $z \sim$~0.8,~1.47 and 2.23, respectively.
Our targets are distributed across the HiZELS fields: the UKIDSS UDS and SA22 fields, the COSMOS field and the Bo{\"o}tes field (see Table \ref{fields_numbers}). For full details on the catalogues, see \cite{Sobral.13} and \cite{Sobral15}.






